revertTCPs(Plan) - Static method in class gov.nasa.larcfm.Util.PlanUtil
Deprecated.
Returns a Plan with TCPs removed between start and upto. If it was a kinematic plan, this will attempt to regress the TCPs to their original source points and times (if the proper metadata is available). Note. No check is made to insure that start or upto is not in the middle of a TCP. Note. See also Plan.revertGroupOfTCPs which uses sourcePosition but not sourceTimes. It seeks to retain ground speeds. Warning: The reversion of points later in a plan without reverting earlier points can lead to strange ground speeds, because the source times correspond to longer paths (without turns).
